<p>One can check that in the continuous case this is such that <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msubsup><mi>F</mi><mrow><mover accent="true"><mi>x</mi><mo>âƒ—</mo></mover><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi>i</mi></mrow><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">â€²</mo></msubsup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msub><mover accent="true"><mi>x</mi><mo>âƒ—</mo></mover><mi>i</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">âˆ‚</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">/</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">âˆ‚</mi><msub><mi>x</mi><mi>i</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mi>f</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mover accent="true"><mi>x</mi><mo>âƒ—</mo></mover><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">F_{\vec x,
