style="height:0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;"></span><span class="mrel">âˆ£</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;"></span><span class="mord mathdefault">i</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;"></span><span class="mrel">âˆˆ</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;"></span><span class="mopen">[</span><span class="mord">âˆ£</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right:0.14643em;">X</span></span><span class="mord">âˆ£</span><span class="mclose">]</span><span class="mclose">}</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">â€‹</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height:1.2990000000000002em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>

<p>The above implies that when we define the operator norm, the <em>particular</em> norm
we choose on the domain does not really matter (as long as it is not the
<span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant="normal">â„“</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">âˆ</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\ell_\infty</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height:0.84444em;vertical-align:-0.15em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord">â„“</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height:0.151392em;"><span style="top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height:2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">âˆ</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">â€‹</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height:0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> norm), as the elements of norm exactly 1 will always be
precisely the standard basis of the â€œoverlyingâ€ vector space.
For this reason, we will write:</p>

<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mtable rowspacing="0.24999999999999992em" columnalign="right left" columnspacing="0em"><mtr><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="true"><mrow><mo stretchy="false">âˆ¥</mo><mi>M</mi><msub><mo stretchy="false">âˆ¥</mo><mi>p</mi></msub></mrow></mstyle></mtd><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="true"><mrow><mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mi>sup</mi><mo>â¡</mo><mo stretchy="false">{</mo><mo stretchy="false">âˆ¥</mo><mi>M</mi><mi>v</mi><msub><mo stretchy="false">âˆ¥</mo><mi>p</mi></msub><mo>âˆ£</mo><mi>v</mi><mo>âˆˆ</mo><msup><mi mathvariant="double-struck">N</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">âˆ£</mi><mi mathvariant="script">X</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">âˆ£</mi></mrow></msup><mo separator="true">,</mo><mo stretchy="false">âˆ¥</mo><mi>v</mi><msub><mo stretchy="false">âˆ¥</mo><mi>p</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy="false">}</mo></mrow></mstyle></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="true"><mrow></mrow></mstyle></mtd><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="true"><mrow><mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mi>sup</mi><mo>â¡</mo><mo stretchy="false">{</mo><mo stretchy="false">âˆ¥</mo><mi>M</mi><mi>v</mi><msub><mo stretchy="false">âˆ¥</mo><mi>p</mi></msub><mo>âˆ£</mo><mi>v</mi><mo>âˆˆ</mo><mo stretchy="false">{</mo><msub><mi>e</mi><mi>i</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">}</mo><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi>i</mi><mo>âˆˆ</mo><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">âˆ£</mi><mi mathvariant="script">X</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">âˆ£</mi><mo stretchy="false">]</mo><mo stretchy="false">}</mo></mrow></mstyle></mtd></mtr></mtable><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\begin{aligned}
\lVert M\rVert_p &amp;= \sup\{\lVert Mv\rVert_p \mid
v\in\mathbb{N}^{|\mathcal{X}|}, \lVert v\rVert_p = 1\}\\
&amp;= \sup\{\lVert Mv\rVert_p \mid v\in\{e_i\}, i\in[|\mathcal{X}|]\}
\end{aligned}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height:3.0980000000000003em;vertical-align:-1.2990000000000002em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mtable"><span class="col-align-r"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height:1.7990000000000002em;"><span style="top:-3.861em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height:3em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mopen">âˆ¥</span><span class="mord mathdefault" style="margin-right:0.10903em;">M</span><span class="mclose"><span class="mclose">âˆ¥</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height:0.15139200000000003em;"><span style="top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height:2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathdefault mtight">p</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">â€‹</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height:0.286108em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span style="top:-2.3609999999999998em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height:3em;"></span><span class="mord"></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">â€‹</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height:1.2990000000000002em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="col-align-l"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height:1.7990000000000002em;"><span style="top:-3.861em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height:3em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord"></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;"></span><span class="mop">sup</span><span class="mopen">{</span><span class="mopen">âˆ¥</span><span class="mord