<p>The proof is rather straightforward.
By the characteriation of norm-1 elements of <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi mathvariant="double-struck">N</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">âˆ£</mi><mi mathvariant="script">X</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">âˆ£</mi></mrow></msup></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\mathbb{N}^{|\mathcal{X}|}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height:0.8879999999999999em;vertical-align:0em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathbb">N</span></span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height:0.8879999999999999em;"><span style="top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height:2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mtight">âˆ£</span><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mathcal mtight" style="margin-right:0.14643em;">X</span></span><span class="mord mtight">âˆ£</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>, we
have that the operator norm will be:</p>

<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy="false">âˆ¥</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">âˆ‡</mi><mi>f</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mover accent="true"><mi>x</mi><mo>âƒ—</mo></mover><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><msub><mo stretchy="false">âˆ¥</mo><mi>p</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>sup</mi><mo>â¡</mo><mo stretchy="false">{</mo><mo stretchy="false">âˆ¥</mo><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">âˆ‡</mi><mi>f</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mover accent="true"><mi>x</mi><mo>âƒ—</mo></mover><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo stretchy="false">]</mo><msub><mi>e</mi><mi>i</mi></msub><msub><mo stretchy="false">âˆ¥</mo><mi>p</mi></msub><mo>âˆ£</mo><mi>i</mi><mo>âˆˆ</mo><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">âˆ£</mi><mi mathvariant="script">X</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">âˆ£</mi><mo stretchy="false">]</mo><mo stretchy="false">}</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\lVert \nabla f(\vec x)\rVert_p = \sup\{\lVert [\nabla f(\vec x)] e_i\rVert_p\mid i\in[|\mathcal{X}|]\}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height:1.036108em;vertical-align:-0.286108em;"></span><span class="mopen">âˆ¥</span><span class="mord">âˆ‡</span><span class="mord mathdefault" style="margin-right:0.10764em;">f</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord accent"><span class="vlist-t"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height:0.714em;"><span style="top:-3em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height:3em;"></span><span class="mord mathdefault">x</span></span><span style="top:-3em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height:3em;"></span><span class="accent-body" style="left:-0.20772em;"><span class="overlay" style="height:0.714em;width:0.471em;"><svg width='0.471em' height='0.714em' style='width:0.471em' viewBox='0 0 471 714' preserveAspectRatio='xMinYMin'><path d='M377 20c0-5.3